# Pipeline Standards

## Idempotent Ingestion

Every ingestion script must be safe to re-run without duplicating data. Use one of these strategies:

- UPSERT (INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE) when the source provides a natural key
- DELETE + INSERT for the current batch window (e.g., delete today's rows then re-insert)
- Track last-ingested timestamp and only fetch newer records

Never blindly INSERT into a table that may already contain the same rows.

## Type Hints

Use type hints on all function signatures. Prefer built-in generics (dict, list, str | None) over typing module imports when on Python 3.12+.

```python
# good
def fetch_observations(state: str, date: str | None = None) -> list[dict]:

# avoid
def fetch_observations(state, date=None):
```
